      "writtenOn": "2018-02-16T00:11:41Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Also I think locks are required anyway, since Write(...) is not guaranteed to be atomic (so two concurrent writes can lean to gibberish).\n\nSo something like:\n\ntype config struct {\n  l sync.Mutex\n  out io.Writer\n}\n\ntype jsonLogger struct {\n  ctx context.Context\n  cfg *config\n}\n\nfunc (l *jsonLogger) LogCall(...) {\n  blob, err :\u003d json.Marshal(...)\n  ...\n\n  l.cfg.l.Lock()\n  defer l.cfg.l.Unlock()\n  err :\u003d l.cfg.out.Write(blob)\n  ...\n}",
